Timothy Harleth has been selected as the White House Chief Usher by First Lady Melania Trump. In this role, he will oversee more than 90 White House Residence staff. Harleth brings over a decade of hospitality and leadership experience to the position, having served as the director of rooms at the Trump International Hotel in Washington, D.C., and in various management positions at the Mandarin Oriental in Washington, D.C., and New York. He will begin his new role on July 3, 2017.